parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank leaks and fractures can cause fuel to spill onto the ground, creating a fire hazard, especially in the presence of an ignition source. This can lead to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: fuel dripping from the filler neck
pool of gasoline under the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Erratic fuel sensors can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to unexpected fuel depletion, engine stalling, and increased risk of accidents, especially on busy roads or in hazardous weather conditions.
symptoms: running out of gas without warning
hesitation or difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant leaks, engine misfires, and stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the rocker arm bolts can cause engine misfires, stalling, and head damage, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the passlock system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while in operation, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling or shutting down while in operation

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can lead to reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: brake light bulbs burn out frequently
terminals no longer make contact in the sockets.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including stalling, loss of power, and fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Malfunctioning sliding doors can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if they open while the vehicle is in motion.
Airbag system failures can increase the risk of injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause startle, distraction, and loss of control, leading to accidents or injuries. It can also cause physical harm to occupants.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without a crash or collision

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ineffective seatbelts can fail to restrain occupants in a crash, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Seatbelts do not hold occupants in the upright position
